46:16.615 --> 46:29.170
I was a pastor for 33 of those and I watched a lot of tragedies, unspeakable disappointments in life.

46:31.298 --> 46:32.780
A lot of babies died.

46:38.187 --> 46:42.693
A lot of accidents on motorcycles, a handful of suicides.

46:46.177 --> 46:55.950
The people who embraced the sovereignty of God and its mysteries did not go insane.

46:55.990 --> 46:59.154
And they said that was the reason.

47:00.386 --> 47:08.277
I have heard it from young mothers so many times I cannot not be excited about these doctrines.

47:11.201 --> 47:17.731
The rock on which we stand is simply massively unshakable and glorious.

47:18.191 --> 47:19.714
We don't have all the answers.

47:20.715 --> 47:23.259
That's not what this seminar is about.

47:23.279 --> 47:28.466
Every question about the sovereignty of God and the mysteries of the will of man

47:29.378 --> 47:31.721
The question is, what is true in the Bible?

47:32.743 --> 47:35.267
And can I stand on it in the worst of times?

47:36.929 --> 47:38.431
That's the way Johnny experiences.

47:38.732 --> 47:40.174
Now, watch this.

47:40.855 --> 47:46.723
Johnny's spiritual formation was largely influenced by Puritans and Reform pastors and theologians.

47:46.763 --> 47:48.225
So Puritans, they're all Calvinists.

47:48.466 --> 47:51.010
Reform means Calvinists and theologians.

47:51.110 --> 47:54.815
Johnny sat on the back porch of the family farm and listened to R.C.

47:54.895 --> 47:56.818
Sproul, modern day

47:56.930 --> 48:06.466
Puritan Calvinist, going to be with Jesus, John Gerstner, his teacher, Calvinist lover of Jonathan Edwards, modern Calvinist who strengthened her positions on the sovereignty of God.

48:06.707 --> 48:10.153
So John Sloan is going out of his way to get Johnny in trouble.

48:12.737 --> 48:14.039
What's up, Sloan?

48:16.464 --> 48:18.908
Ms. Erickson became a five-point Calvinist.

48:18.928 --> 48:22.514
I read that, I said, you're kidding me, you used that word?

48:28.546 --> 48:31.890
She's never called herself a five-point Calvinist out loud.

48:31.930 --> 48:49.368
As far as I know, she usually was reformed and Calvinist, but now in public, probably one of her most popular books on the way that was published in November, and it's introduced by saying, oh, by the way, world.

48:50.149 --> 48:51.651
It's written by a five-point Calvinist.

48:54.774 --> 48:55.875
I'm going to write to her.

48:56.676 --> 48:58.258
I'm going to say, what's up, Johnny?

48:58.978 --> 49:00.541
I did that with John MacArthur.

49:02.004 --> 49:04.488
Remember when MacArthur stood right here?

49:05.831 --> 49:07.694
Was it 1990 or something like that?

49:08.656 --> 49:22.962
And I had noticed, he won't mind me saying this because I've said it in front of thousands of pastors with him sitting beside me, I noticed that in his books he had printed Puritan sermons at the end.

49:23.202 --> 49:30.471
It was a season where about every book that came out, about four or five books, he had Puritan sermons just tacked on for no fair reason.

49:31.532 --> 49:42.244
I thought, John MacArthur is a fundamentalist pre-trib, pre-mill anti-Calvinist.

49:43.806 --> 49:48.592
He's not a, I mean anti-charismatic, right?

49:48.612 --> 49:50.354
He's not a Calvinist, is he?

49:51.170 --> 50:00.564
So I invite him to come to the pastor's conference and speak to find out.

50:00.584 --> 50:06.893
And he spoke and then the Q and A. I'm sitting right about over there in this room.

50:07.694 --> 50:18.450
And I said, Dr. MacArthur, I noticed that at the end of the last Tuesday books that you just published, there's Puritan sermons.

50:20.226 --> 50:22.788
Are you a five point Calvinist?

50:23.069 --> 50:24.931
So this is in front of about 400 pastors.

50:26.472 --> 50:27.553
This is like coming out.

50:33.639 --> 50:39.625
And he paused and he said, yes, to gasps.

50:41.387 --> 50:43.989
I said, so why haven't you said so for the last 40 years?

50:46.752 --> 50:49.074
And he said, sometimes you have to get old enough.

50:51.106 --> 50:54.610
to be wise and bold and straight.

50:54.630 --> 50:57.152
I don't know exactly words, those are my words, something like that.

50:58.274 --> 51:03.519
So maybe Johnny will, I don't know what she'll say, but I found this shocking.

51:04.941 --> 51:08.624
Like, Bethlehem, of course they do seminars on five point calendar.

51:08.644 --> 51:09.345
That's what we do.

51:10.226 --> 51:11.327
We've done this for 40 years.

51:11.347 --> 51:13.550
This is not surprising to anybody.

51:14.791 --> 51:17.714
Johnny, in the introduction to the most

51:17.922 --> 51:23.508
a beautiful devotional book that will be read across the theological spectrum.

51:25.310 --> 51:42.770
Many theological tributaries helped fill the river of this woman's love for Christ, but God's word and her afflictions, God's word and her afflictions are the main source of her adoration and devotion to Jesus Christ.

51:43.350 --> 51:46.834
I confess, this is John Sloan talking now, knowing her for 40 years or so,

51:47.266 --> 52:01.906
I confess I have never met anyone who has the kind of constant communication with Jesus Christ that Johnny experiences.

52:02.788 --> 52:13.362
All I want you to hear from that is Calvinism saves her life to this very day at age 74 getting ready to meet Jesus.

52:14.404 --> 52:16.146
She's going to wave that flag

52:16.962 --> 52:25.011
and it is the means by which he has the closest communication with Jesus of anybody that John Slaughan knows.

52:26.993 --> 52:42.770
So if you think Calvinism does not have that kind of sweet, personal, practical, life-saving, saving daily effect, you need to stay in the seminar for five more weeks, six more.

52:46.690 --> 52:47.631
We got 15 minutes.

52:48.312 --> 52:48.792
Where are we?

52:50.735 --> 52:55.840
One more illustration.

52:55.860 --> 52:57.322
Good many of you know this person.

52:57.362 --> 53:00.606
I don't think they'd mind if I gave you their name, but I'll just let you figure it out.

53:03.129 --> 53:06.152
In December of 1987, he wrote me this letter.

53:07.393 --> 53:09.516
My father died unexpectedly at age 63.

53:09.856 --> 53:14.962
I was plunged into a journey of several months struggling

53:15.106 --> 53:16.748
to understand what had happened.

53:17.949 --> 53:27.559
I was at Bethlehem, but new, but new to the teaching and apparently missing many of the distinctives.

53:28.319 --> 53:30.582
He's talking about Reformed theology.

53:30.982 --> 53:36.448
He was too new and some of you are too new here to know what I'm talking about.

53:37.008 --> 53:42.674
And this is going to be your baths in the sovereignty of God, your immersion.

53:43.714 --> 53:53.450
Fast forward to 1992, so from 87 to 92, we had been in China for a year and returned home to have our first child.

53:55.153 --> 54:01.624
As you remember, she lived one day and died in our arms.

54:04.168 --> 54:10.258
It was then that the teaching of God's providence came home to roost.

54:11.426 --> 54:40.530
God had not turned us loose to some natural events, but in His divine mercy had seen fit to give us a child and through the process of taking her from us work in us a honing and sanctifying unlike anything we had ever known.

54:42.626 --> 55:00.563
Thanks to the foundation laid in my life through our years at Bethlehem, I was now able to embrace and understand such verses as the Lord gifts and the Lord takes away.

55:01.765 --> 55:05.088
Blessed be the name of the Lord.

55:05.488 --> 55:09.372
That's what Kenny wants me to teach this and wants to be a part of this.

55:09.933 --> 55:11.474
That's the kind of people we want.

55:11.906 --> 55:17.014
I was sitting right on the front pew there where one of our missionaries on the Middle East came back.

55:17.796 --> 55:18.898
They had gone to Turkey.

55:19.218 --> 55:20.420
Many of you will know who this is.

55:21.322 --> 55:23.085
They're going to Turkey to have their first baby.

55:23.645 --> 55:28.013
The baby died as she was giving birth.

55:28.033 --> 55:30.116
And they came back here, arms empty.

55:31.198 --> 55:35.265
It was the very first Sunday that we ever sang.

55:36.206 --> 55:38.450
Blessed be the name of the Lord.

55:39.618 --> 55:43.364
I'm standing there and they're sitting right there in the second or third pew.

55:45.186 --> 55:47.550
He gives and takes away.

55:48.211 --> 55:50.594
He gives and takes away.

55:51.095 --> 55:56.182
My heart has learned to say, how blessed is your name?

55:57.785 --> 56:02.592
And their hands were like this.

56:02.612 --> 56:05.777
Totally submitted to the sovereignty of God.

56:05.797 --> 56:06.738
They're back there now.

56:07.010 --> 56:07.992
You want me to find out who this is?

56:08.012 --> 56:10.535
Go find out who's in the Middle East, right?

56:10.555 --> 56:11.397
They're back there now.

56:11.837 --> 56:13.840
Got lots of kids now.

56:13.860 --> 56:23.115
They came through and they came through and that song, you know, I sometimes wonder when you sing that song with 30,000 students at passion, does he have any idea what they're saying?

56:24.256 --> 56:27.922
Because they sing it like, like it's a cheerleading song.

56:30.145 --> 56:33.170
And I said to our worship leaders, you know, if we ever sing that song,

56:34.690 --> 56:43.542
Chuck won't remember this, but if we ever sing that song, when we get to that chorus, let the drums drop out.

56:43.562 --> 56:45.304
We're talking about dead babies.

56:46.285 --> 56:52.193
We're talking about dead babies, or 10 children wiped away in a hurricane.

56:52.814 --> 56:54.696
You don't see it like that.

56:54.716 --> 56:58.782
He gives and takes away.

56:59.603 --> 57:00.884
He gives and takes away.

57:00.904 --> 57:02.226
That's how you sing it.

57:05.538 --> 57:07.721
Okay, that's introduction.

57:09.764 --> 57:10.265
10 minutes.

57:13.931 --> 57:17.256
Why in the world are you starting with I?

57:18.237 --> 57:34.322
T-U-L-I-P. Total depravity, unconditional election, limited atonement, irresistible grace, perseverance of the saints, and Piper starts with

57:35.458 --> 57:42.165
I, not T, or you, or L, or P, why?

57:44.006 --> 57:44.447
Here's why.

57:49.131 --> 58:04.306
My practical experience of getting people over the hump of their initial indignation at the thought that God and not themselves was decisive,

58:04.866 --> 58:06.968
in their coming to Christ.

58:08.290 --> 58:11.393
God was decisive, not their free will.

58:13.535 --> 58:22.225
My discovery in dealing with folks in helping overcome that hump is to ask them how they got saved.

58:24.487 --> 58:25.449
Give me an illustration.

58:26.850 --> 58:34.098
So in this sanctuary, I preached a message in which I don't remember the text, but the point was pretty clear that God is sovereign,

58:34.274 --> 58:42.744
If you came to Christ, God was decisive in that act, not you, and you should be giving Him eternal thanks and singing amazing grace.

58:43.185 --> 58:45.187
I once was blind, but now I see.

58:46.449 --> 58:48.652
That should be your song for the rest of eternity.

58:50.234 --> 58:53.798
She came up afterwards and she said, I can't handle that.

58:54.919 --> 58:57.242
I cannot handle that.

58:57.623 --> 59:03.730
God decides who is saved and who's not rescued from their blindness.

59:06.530 --> 59:08.813
I said, look, I know where you live in Phillips.

59:09.153 --> 59:09.574
Hang on.

59:09.914 --> 59:10.575
You're walking home?

59:10.835 --> 59:11.035
Yes.

59:11.556 --> 59:12.337
I'm walking home, too.

59:12.637 --> 59:13.318
Let's walk together.

59:14.019 --> 59:15.481
So we walk across the bridge.

59:15.741 --> 59:16.402
I can picture it.

59:17.283 --> 59:22.189
And I said, tell me about coming to Christ.

59:22.910 --> 59:24.852
She's probably 26, 27 years old.

59:25.453 --> 59:26.574
Tell me how you came to Christ.

59:27.635 --> 59:28.777
She was very candid.

59:28.797 --> 59:36.466
She said, when I was about 12, I was the tallest kid in the class.

59:36.770 --> 59:40.975
tall of the boys, tall of the girls, and it was awful.

59:43.298 --> 59:44.720
And I was walking home one day.

59:44.740 --> 59:45.842
I grew up in a Christian home.

59:45.862 --> 59:56.175
I was walking home one day, and some girls started talking down to me and making fun of me as the giant in the class.

01:00:00.340 --> 01:00:04.626
And I felt like I came to a crisis of faith at that moment

01:00:05.218 --> 01:00:10.744
If God is real and loves me, that doesn't matter.

01:00:10.764 --> 01:00:14.088
And if he's not, that matters a lot and I don't like it.

01:00:16.670 --> 01:00:22.316
And I decided God's real and that doesn't matter.

01:00:23.458 --> 01:00:23.938
I'm his.

01:00:24.959 --> 01:00:26.841
I think that's where I got saved.

01:00:27.382 --> 01:00:28.863
Or at least that's where I knew I was saved.

01:00:30.025 --> 01:00:31.767
And I said, that's amazing.

01:00:31.847 --> 01:00:33.048
That's beautiful.

01:00:34.069 --> 01:00:34.930
Now really,

01:00:35.490 --> 01:00:38.093
Let's call her Jane, really Jane.

01:00:39.055 --> 01:00:54.676
At that moment, you think you were smart enough, spiritual enough, wise enough to make that glorious discovery and commitment happen, and that wasn't to give from God.

01:00:56.398 --> 01:00:58.461
And she said, well, I don't think I'd want to say that.

01:00:58.481 --> 01:01:01.585
I said, that's all, that's my Calvinism in a nutshell.

01:01:04.288 --> 01:01:05.490
I wouldn't want to say that.

01:01:06.786 --> 01:01:07.507
I don't either.

01:01:08.289 --> 01:01:11.695
When I get to heaven and God says, why are you here?

01:01:11.835 --> 01:01:13.358
I say, I trusted your son.

01:01:13.899 --> 01:01:15.602
And he says, why do you trust my son?

01:01:19.328 --> 01:01:20.791
He does not want to hear the answer.

01:01:21.031 --> 01:01:26.481
I'm smart.

01:01:26.541 --> 01:01:27.763
What answer does he want to hear?

01:01:30.708 --> 01:01:31.730
By the grace of God.

01:01:35.714 --> 01:01:39.157
of the grace of God, I am what I am.

01:01:39.177 --> 01:02:03.922
The definition of irresistible grace is, this is my definition, it's not written down in any book, it might be, irresistible grace is the act of God by which he overcomes all resistance and unfailingly, infallibly, definitely surely, certainly,

01:02:04.674 --> 01:02:10.621
causes a person to see the truth and worth of Christ as compelling.

01:02:13.865 --> 01:02:21.935
So that he, the person, embraces Christ as his supremely treasured Savior and Lord.

01:02:29.043 --> 01:02:30.105
That's a weighty sentence.

01:02:32.047 --> 01:02:34.450
So here's his double grace is the act of God

01:02:35.426 --> 01:02:39.010
by which he overcomes all resistance.

01:02:39.070 --> 01:02:39.851
Now, let's just stop there.

01:02:39.911 --> 01:02:43.636
We'll spend the rest of our five minutes on that, probably, because it's right here.

01:02:44.197 --> 01:02:50.424
Because I don't want you to stumble and say, I should have said already about say it now.

01:02:51.806 --> 01:03:01.557
I don't really give a hoot about the system of Calvinism as an authority or a criterion of truth.

01:03:03.660 --> 01:03:05.362
This is the authority.

01:03:06.178 --> 01:03:08.261
This is the criteria of truth.

01:03:08.862 --> 01:03:11.206
If Calvinism matches, I believe it.

01:03:11.407 --> 01:03:12.469
If it doesn't, I don't.

01:03:12.929 --> 01:03:13.390
Is that clear?

01:03:13.851 --> 01:03:14.252
You got that?

01:03:14.973 --> 01:03:17.617
This is the truth.

01:03:18.078 --> 01:03:20.542
So, I'm assuming that's the way most of you think.

01:03:20.562 --> 01:03:21.383
You're Bible people.

01:03:22.766 --> 01:03:27.814
And if you're not Bible people, be a Bible person.

01:03:27.834 --> 01:03:29.397
Measure Piper by the Bible.

01:03:29.497 --> 01:03:30.098
He's not

01:03:30.178 --> 01:03:30.779
God.

01:03:30.819 --> 01:03:31.961
He's fallible.

01:03:32.001 --> 01:03:32.963
He's sinful.

01:03:33.424 --> 01:03:34.626
He's finite.

01:03:34.706 --> 01:03:36.369
He's culturally conditioned.

01:03:36.629 --> 01:03:37.531
Good grief.

01:03:37.551 --> 01:03:38.252
Why are you in here?

01:03:43.742 --> 01:03:48.871
But if it's in the Bible, live and die by it.

01:03:48.891 --> 01:03:50.313
So are you Bible people?

01:03:50.894 --> 01:03:55.442
When you hear the term irresistible grace, what's your first thought from the Bible?

01:03:58.210 --> 01:04:00.413
The Bible says we resist.

01:04:01.914 --> 01:04:03.456
How can you call it irresistible?

01:04:03.496 --> 01:04:06.560
The Bible says again and again, we resist grace.

01:04:06.640 --> 01:04:08.081
We resist the Holy Spirit.

01:04:08.622 --> 01:04:09.843
Give me a break, Piper.

01:04:10.364 --> 01:04:12.246
Get biblical.

01:04:14.048 --> 01:04:17.152
That's why this first part is so important.

01:04:17.172 --> 01:04:22.117
The term irresistible grace was never meant to mean you can't resist grace.

01:04:23.959 --> 01:04:26.322
It just means you can't successfully

01:04:26.434 --> 01:04:28.316
resist sovereign grace.

01:04:28.837 --> 01:04:31.539
You can resist for a year or two, or 10 or 20.

01:04:32.360 --> 01:04:33.782
If he wants you, he'll have you.

01:04:35.283 --> 01:04:35.984
He'll overcome it.

01:04:36.004 --> 01:04:37.406
So let's just see some texts.

01:04:38.447 --> 01:04:46.355
You men who are stiff neck, this is Stephen talking, and uncircumcised in heart and ears are always resisting the Holy Spirit.

01:04:47.116 --> 01:04:49.098
You're doing just what your fathers did.

01:04:49.138 --> 01:04:52.722
So we can resist the Holy Spirit.

01:04:53.090 --> 01:04:54.492
We can resist grace.

01:04:54.732 --> 01:04:55.353
Yes, you can.

01:04:55.574 --> 01:04:57.637
Some of you are doing that right now tonight.

01:04:58.418 --> 01:05:01.002
In some area of your life, you're just resistant.

01:05:01.282 --> 01:05:03.986
Grace wants to do this and you know, no, no, no.

01:05:04.027 --> 01:05:05.068
I'm not going to do it.

01:05:05.088 --> 01:05:08.493
I'm not going to yield to that movement of the Holy Spirit.

01:05:09.915 --> 01:05:10.476
Well, guess what?

01:05:10.697 --> 01:05:11.257
He's God.

01:05:15.684 --> 01:05:19.390
Do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God by whom you were sealed.

01:05:19.951 --> 01:05:22.194
You can grieve the Holy Spirit.

01:05:22.690 --> 01:05:24.132
That's worth all seminar.

01:05:25.534 --> 01:05:26.576
Grieve God.

01:05:27.617 --> 01:05:28.198
Oh my goodness.

01:05:28.960 --> 01:05:29.580
What a mystery.

01:05:31.283 --> 01:05:33.366
His children can grieve God.

01:05:35.169 --> 01:05:36.972
Do not quench the Holy Spirit.

01:05:36.992 --> 01:05:38.855
You can quench the Holy Spirit.

01:05:39.816 --> 01:05:40.677
You can resist.

01:05:41.439 --> 01:05:42.380
You can grieve.

01:05:43.021 --> 01:05:44.143
You can quench.

01:05:46.046 --> 01:05:46.386
Or

01:05:47.938 --> 01:05:53.804
But answer Israel, he says, all day long, I have stretched out my hands to a disobedient and obstinate people.

01:05:55.126 --> 01:05:59.270
God's hands are like this and they're obstinate.

01:06:04.436 --> 01:06:17.650
So that's why I say, irresistible grace is the act of God by which he overcomes

01:06:18.114 --> 01:06:19.556
all resistance.

01:06:21.598 --> 01:06:31.070
And unfailingly causes a person to see the truth and the worth of Christ as compelling.

01:06:33.253 --> 01:06:34.695
And they're done resisting.

01:06:34.715 --> 01:06:35.055
They're done.

01:06:35.976 --> 01:06:37.298
So just think how you got saved.

01:06:38.199 --> 01:06:41.583
I mean, many of you in this room like me got saved so early you can't remember it.

01:06:42.304 --> 01:06:42.845
That's okay.

01:06:42.945 --> 01:06:43.826
I don't remember

01:06:44.194 --> 01:06:45.175
those moments.

01:06:45.456 --> 01:06:46.997
My mother talked to me about them.

01:06:47.278 --> 01:06:48.279
I take a second hand.

01:06:49.340 --> 01:06:54.667
I judge the certainty of my salvation, not on the memory of my conversion, but on the reality of Christ today.

01:06:54.727 --> 01:06:56.750
That's how I live.

01:06:56.970 --> 01:06:59.213
But many of you remember how you got saved.

01:06:59.653 --> 01:07:07.123
And if you're honest, at one point the day before Christ was not compelling.

01:07:07.603 --> 01:07:11.208
He was boring, this interesting question, skepticism.

01:07:11.268 --> 01:07:13.170
Next day,

01:07:13.570 --> 01:07:14.631
or in the middle of the night?

01:07:17.594 --> 01:07:18.195
He's real.

01:07:20.357 --> 01:07:20.938
What was that?

01:07:22.019 --> 01:07:22.880
What just happened?

01:07:24.361 --> 01:07:25.322
He's compelling.

01:07:25.603 --> 01:07:27.264
I can't not trust Him.

01:07:27.304 --> 01:07:31.268
I can't walk away from this portrait in the New Testament.

01:07:31.308 --> 01:07:35.072
It's too glorious, too beautiful, too compelling.

01:07:35.112 --> 01:07:36.994
What just happened?

01:07:37.355 --> 01:07:38.216
I'll tell you what happened.

01:07:38.816 --> 01:07:40.498
Sovereign grace just happened.

01:07:42.498 --> 01:07:43.559
and you will praise it.

01:07:44.561 --> 01:07:51.249
I do hope that when you sing amazing grace, how sweet the sound is saved, a wretch like me, that's what you mean.

01:07:51.329 --> 01:07:55.974
So that's where we're gonna pick it up next week.

01:07:55.995 --> 01:07:59.819
I've got seven arguments, and we haven't seen any of them yet.

01:08:00.700 --> 01:08:02.803
We haven't even started the seminar yet.

01:08:04.986 --> 01:08:08.350
I've got seven arguments for irresistible grace.

01:08:08.630 --> 01:08:11.954
You'll have plenty of chance of hope next time to

01:08:12.034 --> 01:08:15.158
Ask questions about those biblical arguments.

01:08:15.278 --> 01:08:17.261
But for now, let's pray.

01:08:17.602 --> 01:08:21.988
And I will make sure you get out on time so you might want to come back.

01:08:22.909 --> 01:08:25.132
Let's pray.

01:08:25.152 --> 01:08:27.435
Father, in heaven, we all have things to do.

01:08:28.417 --> 01:08:36.588
And I pray now that those things would be caught up into the greatness of your person.

01:08:37.750 --> 01:08:38.350
You are.

01:08:39.352 --> 01:08:40.914
You are great.

01:08:41.538 --> 01:09:02.039
You govern all things and you overcame John Piper's and every Christian in this room, you overcame our natural resistance to yourself, to the gospel, to Jesus and how thankful we are.

01:09:03.100 --> 01:09:09.106
Dismiss these friends with your blessing, bring them safely home, fill their homes with

01:09:09.378 --> 01:09:22.275
joy and truth and love and peace and save those in this room that are outside Christ and make us emissaries of salvation everywhere we go.

01:09:22.315 --> 01:09:24.341
We pray in Jesus name.

01:09:24.361 --> 01:09:24.722
Amen.

